        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
           <span>non-Hermitian Physics</span>
        </h3>
        <ol class="text-base-content/80 mb-6 list-decimal pl-4">
          <li>
            <strong>non-Hermitian Bloch Oscillation</strong><br>
            We investigate the Bloch Oscillation (BO) in non-Hermitian Hatano-Nelson (HN) model. The non-reciprocal hoppings in HN model 
            can lead to non-Hermitian skin effect (NHSE) while electric field will lead to Wannier-Strak localization (WSL). The competition 
            between them will enrich wavepacket dynamics such as asymmetric Bloch oscillation and some novel edge dynamics. We derive 
            the semiclassical equations of motion to describe wavepacket dynamics and have observed these
            phenomena in acoustic lattices.
          </li>     
          <li>
            <strong>Chiral Landau-Zener Tunneling</strong><br>
            Wannier-Stark exceptional points (EPs) in non-Hermtian SSH model under a uniform electric field can induce chiral Landau-Zener 
            tunneling, which has a tight relation with Floquet EPs (Longhi, PRL, 2022). We design the acoustic lattice to experimentally 
            demonstrate such effect.
          </li>      
          <li>
            <strong>Twinkling Bloch Oscillation</strong><br>
            We considered BO in anti-Hermitian HN lattices. The purely imaginary band due to anti-Hermicity can give a zero group velocity, 
            which will freeze the motion in real space. However, the nonzero imaginary part of spectrum gives a normalizaiton oscillation like 
            twinkling stars visually. We have observed TBO in acoustic lattices. And this effect can be extended to long-range coupling system to 
            obtain what we name "pseudo-fractional" Bloch oscillation. 
          </li>    
        </ol>

